{"questionId":"11941","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The matrix A is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  3&amp;0 \\\\   0&amp;2  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Pentagon, P, which has an area of 7 cm<sup>2</sup>, is transformed by A.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The matrix B is defined by&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"B = \\frac{1}{2}\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {3\\sqrt 3 }&amp;3 \\\\   { - 2}&amp;{2\\sqrt 3 }  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>B</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n              <msqrt>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n              </msqrt>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <msqrt>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n              </msqrt>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p>B represents the combined effect of the transformation represented by a matrix X, followed by the transformation represented by A.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Describe fully the geometrical transformation represented by X.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Rotation&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>clockwise by 30° about the origin &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11941","referenceCode":"EXM.2.AHL.TZ0.15d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Describe fully the geometrical transformation represented by X.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.9—Matrix transformations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}